Floriography: auspicious, passionate, lucky.

Aechmea chantinii 'Samuri' is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bromeliaceae, subfamily Bromelioideae. The genus, named for the Swedish botanist, zoologist, and anatomist Gustaf Johan Billberg. Leaves of Aechmea chantinii 'Samuri' smooth and orderly arranged as a loose lotus flower. Inflorescence, growing from the middle of leaves, composes of bright colorful bracts and build a unique shape. Aechmea chantinii 'Samuri' plants are widely grew in flower beds and family yards.

{"production":"China","origin":"Mexico","category":"Bromeliaceae, Billbergia","blooming":"Flowering period mainly in winter and spring, viewing period 1-2 months","floral_language":"Ananas comosus cv. Variegata
Floriography: auspicious, passionate, lucky.

Ananas comosus cv. Variegata is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bromeliaceae, subfamily Bromelioideae. The genus, named for the Swedish botanist, zoologist, and anatomist Gustaf Johan Billberg. Leaves of Ananas comosus cv. Variegata smooth and orderly arranged as a loose lotus flower. Inflorescence, growing from the middle of leaves, composes of bright colorful bracts and build a unique shape. Ananas comosus cv. Variegata plants are widely grew in flower beds and family yards.

These plants grow best in mild sunlight. Bright sunlight should be avoided. Bloom in winter and spring for one to two months.","color":"Bract orange red, leaf color green, leaf edges light yellow"}

Anemone hupehensis var. japonica like sunshine, natural flowering from April to May, with viewing window for 1 to 2 weeks each flower. {"floral_language":"Anisodontea capensis
Floriography: gentle, pure, beautiful 
Anisodontea capensis is a hardy deciduous shrub. Leaf shape is nearly the diamond, and with wavy sawtooth on leaf edges. Flower is bell shape, with single or double petal. Color is pure and fresh quietly elegant. Color includes white, pink, lavender, etc. Hibiscus syriacus is used as a hedge, hedge or garden ornament and indoor plants. 
Anisodontea capensis like plenty of sunshine, a little resistance to shade. Flowering from July to October, with ornamental period, for 2-3 weeks at a time.","origin":"South Africa","production":"China","category":"Malvaceae, Anisodontea","color":"Flower color white, purple, pink","blooming":"Flowering period April-November, viewing period 2-3 weeks"}

Caryota ochlandra Hance is from sub-tropical regions, but with a tropical flavor. It is a tree, bigger and taller than common foliage plants with thick leaves of fine serrated edges shaped like a fish. Often planted as ornamental trees in the yard, street, and parks.

Chrysanthemum is the official flower of Beijing in China. The chrysanthemum is one of the "Four Gentlemen" in flowers in Chinese culture (the others being the plum, the orchid, and bamboo). Extremely popular. In Japan, the chrysanthemum is a symbol of the Emperor and the Imperial family.
Chrysanthemum has many cultivars in different beautiful shapes. Under sunlight, like dazzling little stars in clusters or clumps. Chrysanthemums resist cold weather, even frost, therefore loved by the public in the fall season, and are often well loved by the ancient literati. 
Chrysanthemums like sunny days, mainly blossom in September-November for 3-4 weeks.","blooming":"September-November flowering period, viewing period 3-4 weeks"}

{"floral_language":"Fatsia japonica 
Floriography: sincere, lively, riches and honor
Fatsia japonica is evergreen four seasons. Plant stature is big. Leaves are green, larger, and nearly cordate. Blade edges split into eight angle, like the palm of the hand, thus is named as "eight stars gold plate". It can be planted in the park and artificial hills, also can be potted for beautification household. 
Fatsia japonica likes half overcast environment. Avoid direct sunlight. Two to three hours sunshine in winter. Guzmania lingulata is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bromeliaceae, subfamily Bromelioideae. The genus, named for the Swedish botanist, zoologist, and anatomist Gustaf Johan Billberg. Leaves of Guzmania lingulata smooth and orderly arranged as a loose lotus flower. Inflorescence, growing from the middle of leaves, composes of bright colorful bracts and build a unique shape. Guzmania lingulata plants are widely grew in flower beds and family yards.

basic:
{"production":"China","category":"Compositae, Helianthus","floral_language":"Helianthus annuus
Floriogrphy: sunny, warm, and optimistic.

The name sunflower may derive from the fact that shape of the flower's head resembles the sun, or from the false impression that the blooming plant appears to slowly turn its flower towards the sun as the latter moves across the sky on a daily basis. Generally, there is only a single large golden inflorescence atop an unbranched stem like a small sun. The outer flowers, ray flowers, attract pollinators. The tubiform florets in the center of the flower head, disk flowers, mature into edible fruits (sunflower seeds).

Sunflower prefers sunny areas. The flower can grow in any season, however, summer and winter are better. Blooming period is short, lasting for two through three weeks.","origin":"South America","blooming":"Flowers year around, viewing period 2-3 weeks","color":"Flower color golden yellow , mixed color"}
maintenance: {"size":"Diameter ≥ 10 cm, height ≥ 20 cm","pruning":"Remove yellowing leaves and withered flowers timely","soil":"Peat or soil with specific nutrients","fertilization":"Dilute fertilizers following instructions, every 10-15 days apply fertilizers once","sunlight":"Like sunshine, put in sunny places","watering":"Moderately resistant to drought, keep soil moist, water every 1-2 days in summer, once 3-6 days in autumn and winter"}

{"category":"Calycanthaceae, Chimonanthus","production":"China","blooming":"Flowering period November-March, viewing period 1-2 weeks","color":"Flower color white","floral_language":"Chimonanthus praecox 
Floriography: pride, strong and faithful 
Chimonanthus praecox blossom proudly in the snow, with orchid, bamboo, and chrysanthemum together referred to as the "four gentlemen" in the flower, has been named as the city flower of Wuhan. 
Chimonanthus praecox plant strong firm and pretty. Leaf blade elliptic, flowers are delicate and cabinet. Color is various, petals of 5 single and double. The fragrance of plum blossom is from bitter cold, a symbol of the Chinese nation strong spiritual quality. 
Chimonanthus praecox blossom like the sunshine, summer noon light should be covered. Because of the north-south differences, flowering in December to April of next year, with the ornamental period 1 to 2 weeks.","origin":"China"}

basic:
{"blooming":"Flowering period September-October, viewing period 3-7 days","category":"Leguminosae, Mimosa","color":"Leaf color tender green, flower color white or pink","production":"Southern China","origin":"Tropical Americas","floral_language":"Mimosa pudica 
Floriography: shy, restrained, polite 
Mimosa is pure and fresh and lovely. It is named as shy grass because the leaves will be closed by external touch. 
Shy grass is green color. Leaves are lobular arrangement. Usually four lobules are palmy arrangement and look like a small palm, very lively. With the hand touch or water, petioles prolapse, lobular are closed. After the summer it will flower. Flower is white or pink velvet ball, charming and lovely. 
Mimosa like the sunshine, but avoid direct light. Flowering from September to October, with ornamental period of 3 to 7 days."}

basic:
{"color":"Flower color red, pink, yellow, orange","blooming":"Blooms once every February-March months, viewing period 2-3 weeks","production":"Yunnan","category":"Rosaceae, Rosa","floral_language":"Mini-rose
Mini-rose Fluorography: enthusiasm, brave and independent
Mini-rose is a rose family, was cultivated in the flower kingdom of the Netherlands.
Mini-rose has various colors, and its fragrance is quietly elegant. Inherited the fine quality of the rose family, but with a stature of cabinet and chic, Mini-rose was popular in Europe market at the beginning of the launch, and has become the new favorite of household and desktop decoration. 
Mini-rose likes the sun light, flowering for 2-3 weeks at a time. Bud sprouts after pruning, and under normal circumstances Mini-rose can be perpetual.","origin":"Holland"}
maintenance: {"size":"Diameter ≥ 10 cm, height 15-18 cm","sunlight":"Likes sunshine, put in sunny places, avoid strong sunlight in summer at noon","watering":"Water thoroughly when soil is dry, avoid saturated water","fertilization":"Dilute fertilizers following instructions, apply 2-3 times monthly","pruning":"Remove old, diseased and dead leaves timely, after flowering remove the upper part staring from 5 cm above soil surface, leaving 2-3 leaves","soil":"Peat or soil with specific nutrients"}

Neofinetia falcata, commonly referred to as the Chinese orchid, represents simplicity and serenity.
Neofinetia falcata are graceful with slender leaves and colorful, exotic flowers with pure colors and fragrances, though not as huge as the orchids flowers in the West, but very elegant. For its high ornamental value, often used to decorate rooms.

Neoregelia carolinae 'var. tricolor' is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bromeliaceae, subfamily Bromelioideae. The genus, named for the Swedish botanist, zoologist, and anatomist Gustaf Johan Billberg. Leaves of Neoregelia carolinae 'var. tricolor' smooth and orderly arranged as a loose lotus flower. Inflorescence, growing from the middle of leaves, composes of bright colorful bracts and build a unique shape. {"blooming":"Flowering period year around, viewing period 3-4 weeks","color":"Flower color yellow、white、red、brown","category":"Orchidaceae, Phaius","origin":"China","production":"China","floral_language":"Phaius tankervilleae
Floriography: virtuous, tender, intelligent
Phaius tankervilleae, commonly referred to as the Chinese orchid, represents simplicity and serenity.
Phaius tankervilleae are graceful with slender leaves and colorful, exotic flowers with pure colors and fragrances, though not as huge as the orchids flowers in the West, but very elegant. For its high ornamental value, often used to decorate rooms.
Phaius tankervilleae like half shaded environments. Flowering time differs in different varieties throughout the year with a month-long flowering time, promptly cut the scape after flowering for germination in the next year."}
maintenance: {"soil":"Breathable and loose planting materials with coconut shell, bark or sphagnum moss","size":"Diameter ≥ 10 cm, height ≥ 15 cm","pruning":"Remove old, diseased and dead leaves timely, remove peduncle after flowering","watering":"Water thoroughly when soil is dry, may spray to the ambient environment in summer, reduce watering in winter","fertilization":"Apply fertilizers every 10-15 days in the growing seasons of spring and autumn, foliar fertilizer spray also do good for its growth , fertilize under 10 ℃ (50 ℉) is forbidden","sunlight":"Like half shade, in autumn and winter may take 2-3h sunlight, receive more light when leaves are dark green"}
